# Logs
logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
*.local

# Environment variables (NEVER commit). The .local rule above already
# catches .env.local, but be explicit here too — a stray `.env` or
# `.env.production` should also stay out of the repo. The only env
# file we DO commit is .env.example, kept as a contract for new
# clones to know what variables exist.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Editor directories and files
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea
.DS_Store
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?
